post.description: Create a new Dataset. Use UploadDatasetFile to upload files to the dataset.

x-codeSamples.source:
import os
from lastmile import Lastmile

client = Lastmile(
    bearer_token=os.environ.get("LASTMILE_API_TOKEN"),  # This is the default and can be omitted
)
dataset = client.datasets.create()
print(dataset.dataset)

post.description:
Step 1 of 2: Create a new job configuration for fine-tuning, to be
 subsequently submitted by calling SubmitFineTuneJob.

x-codeSamples.source:
import os
from lastmile import Lastmile

client = Lastmile(
    bearer_token=os.environ.get("LASTMILE_API_TOKEN"),  # This is the default and can be omitted
)
fine_tune_job = client.fine_tune_jobs.create(
    fine_tune_job_config={
        "baseline_model_id": "baselineModelId",
        "selected_columns": ["string", "string", "string"],
        "test_dataset_id": "testDatasetId",
        "train_dataset_id": "trainDatasetId",
    },
)
print(fine_tune_job.job_id)

lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.MetricBa.title: MetricBaseModel
lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.MetricBa.description: Information about a base model corresponding to a metric

lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.ModelFil.title: ModelFile
lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.ModelFil.description: Actual file asset corresponding to a model

lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.User.title: User
lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.User.description: Basic user. TODO: Merge with other notions of a user.

lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.Organiza.title: Organization
lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.Organiza.description:
Organization - collection of Users with shared assets. We do not prescribe
 here any semantics about whether a user can be in more than one organization,
 or any other relationships.

lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.Role.title: Role
lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.Role.description:
A role for a principal (likely a user) within an organization. Mostly used
 for Authorization. Anticipating the need for more roles here, we space out
 the values to leave unused numbers so that we can add more later while
 preserving the natural ordering of permissions. We don't prescribe specific
 authorizations here despite the suggestive names.

lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.Organiza.title: OrganizationRole
lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.Organiza.description:
A role specified in the context of a particular organization. Can be used as
 its own Principal as a convenient way to define groups of permissions.

lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.Principa.title: Principal
lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.Principa.description:
A Principal is an entity in an authorization context, such as a user
 requesting read access to a resource or an organization who owns it.

lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.Subject.title: Subject

datasetId.description: A dataset which a principal may or may not have access to.

modelId.description: A model _definition_ which a principal may or may not have access to.

modelFileId.description:
A model _file_ which a principal may or may not have access to. In
 practice, this likely matches the model itself.

fineTuneJobId.description:
A job, in the sense of an async/worker job. Ex: a user may be able to see
 a fine tune job but not edit/cancel it.

operationId.description:
An operation. Ex: a user may be able to see datasets without their full
 lineage (as operations).

targetPrincipal.description:
A Principal acting as a Subject to express user management actions and
 transitive access. See note in Predicate.

isWildcard.description:
When true, this flag dictates that the Subject represents the entire
 resource type. The `id` field must also be a literal "*" or else we should
 fail validation, to avoid magic strings or unexpected auth configurations.
 A wildcard subject is especially important for creating new resources of a
 type (CREATE), and listing (LIST), since in each case there is no existing
 ID to base authorization on.

lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.Subject.description: A Subject is an entity to which access can be granted, such as a dataset.

lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.Predicat.title: Predicate
lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.Predicat.description:
A Predicate is either a statement or a query of authorization - when a
 Principal, Subject, and Scope are specified, it has a positive or negative
 answer. For example, "can user 4 access resource 9 to write?" or something
 like "user_4:resource_9:write". When the Principal is omitted, it is a
 Clause, and can be used to specify an authorization constraint on a resource.
 For example, simply "resource_9:write", tagging a concrete action with its
 authorization requirements. When the Subject is itself a Principal, the
 Predicate expresses a relation between the Principals. For example, an owner
 user 11 might have write access to a basic user 3, or write access to a whole
 org. Importantly, the target (subject, scope) must have authorization not
 greater than the principal, since the predicate enables "impersonation". So,
 an organization should typically not be authorized to act as an individual
 user this way, since it would confer the same authorization to every member.

lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.Clause.title: Clause
lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.Clause.description:
A Clause is a Predicate not bound to a Principal, specifying a requirement
 for authorization. Example: "dataset_5:write" might represent the "write"
 scope on a resource "dataset_5"

lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.Policy.title: Policy
lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.Policy.description:
A Policy is a disjunction of Clauses, meaning any satisfied Clause is
 sufficient to satisfy the Policy. We don't anticipate needing anything
 sophisticated here, and if we do, this is easily extensible to a complete
 logical algebra.

lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.ChatMess.title: ChatMessage
lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.ChatMess.description: Represents a message from the user or the assistant.

model.description: The ID of the model to use for the completion.

items.description: The list of messages in the conversation so far.

maxTokens.description: The maximum number of tokens to generate.

temperature.description: The temperature to use for the completion.

topP.description: The top_p value to use for the completion.

template.description: The template string that defines the prompt

lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.Dataset.title: Dataset

name.description: Human-readable name for the dataset, if one exists.

description.description: Human-readable description of the dataset, if one exists.

ownerUserId.description: The ID of the user who owns the dataset.

items.description: The columns present in the latest DatasetFile for this dataset

labelState.description: The state of the latest labeling job for the dataset

lmai.proto.model_fine_tuning.v1.Dataset.description:
A Dataset in the most basic sense: metadata and ownership, but nothing tied
 to its data.

id.description: The ID of the dataset file.

datasetId.description: The ID of the corresponding dataset.

id.description: The ID of the dataset file.

index.description: Index of the column within the dataset file.

literalName.description: The literal name for the column.

items.description:
Ordered row values with length always equal to `num_rows` on the
 corresponding view.

labelingStatus.description: The status of the latest general pseudo-labeling job for the dataset

error.description: if the labeling status is error, this field may contain an error message

id.description: The ID of the fine tune job.

name.description: Name corresponding to the fine tuned model derived from this job

baselineModelId.description: The ID for the model used as the starting point for training.

trainDatasetId.description:
The dataset to use for training, with splits baked in or to be
 derived dynamically

testDatasetId.description: The dataset to use for an unbiased evaluation of the model

items.description:
Set of columns to be used in fine-tuning.
 Supported columns: input, output, ground_truth
 For example, a task similar to summarization might need output and
 ground_truth.

trainedModelFile.description: The trained model, if it was created successfully.

resultUrl.description: Url to view the full results and progress (e.g. external W&B url)

lmai.proto.webserver.v2.GetDatasetViewRe.title: GetDatasetViewRequest

datasetId.description:
The ID of the dataset from which to retrieve content. When specified,
 gets data from the current file in the dataset.

datasetFileId.description:
The ID of the (pinned) dataset file from which to retrieve content.
 Requests iterating over pages of results are recommended to use this
 pinned identifier after the first page in order to prevent any effects
 from a dataset changing between the queries.

after.description: Pagination: The index, by row-order, after which to query results.

limit.description: Pagination: The maximum number of results to return on this page.

lmai.proto.webserver.v2.GetDatasetViewRe.description: Get a view of the data within a dataset.

query.description: search query substring match for name and description

totalCount.description:
Total count of datasets which can be listed with applicable
 filters, regardless of page size

downloadUrl.description: The S3 presigned URL to download the dataset file.
